   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE GIFTS PERFECTING THE SAINTS Scripture Reading: Eph 4:7-13 OUTLINE The gifts given by the ascended Head who fills all things vv.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>7-10: Some apostles.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Some prophets.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Some evangelists.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Some shepherds and teachers v. 11.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The gifts perfecting the saints vv.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>12-13: That the saints may participate in the work of the New Testament ministry, which is the building up of the Body of Christ v. 12.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Leading the saints to arrive at the oneness of the faith of the New Testament.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Leading the saints to arrive at the oneness of the full knowledge of the Son of God.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Leading the saints to arrive at a full-grown man in the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Leading the saints to grow into the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ v. 13.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Prayer: Lord, You have brought us out of many preoccupations and have called us into Your name.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Tonight we are all gathered together.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Here we have You, we have Your Spirit, we have Your name, and even more we have Your Word.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Lord, when we read Your Word, we sense Your presence.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>While we are speaking here, may You vindicate that we are one spirit with You.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Speak through our speaking.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>While we speak, may You speak also.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>O Lord, grant us the feeling, and grant us Your thoughts, Your expression, and Your utterance, even a spontaneous and fresh utterance, an utterance that will meet Your need as well as ours.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Lord, what we need is just You.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>You are the Word, and You are the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>You are even our expression and utterance.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Strengthen us within and without, and make our inner man stronger than our outer man.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Lord, may You pour Yourself upon us, and fill us up, nourish us, saturate us, and water us.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Wherever we are, whether we sit on the balcony or on the main floor, may You fill us.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Open up Your Word to every one of us.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Lord, may You teach us mouth to mouth and reveal to us Spirit to spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>May we touch You and Your presence, Your loveliness, and Your grace.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>May everyone present in this meeting feel Your presence with us.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Grant us the warmth, the binding of our wounds, the healing, the recovery, and even the strengthening.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Lord Jesus, we really need You.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>We wait on You from the depth of our being.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Thank You that You have taken the church in Taipei onto the proper track and that it is now going on steadfastly in this new way.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>May You glorify Your name again tonight.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Shame Your enemy, and grant Your blessings to us.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>We bind the evil one, which is Your enemy, by Your victorious name.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Not only do we bind him here in Taipei; we bind him over the whole earth that there would be churches in Your recovery everywhere on earth.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Do destroy all of his evil works and all the dark moves.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>We believe that the cross has overcome the enemy.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Today we declare Your victory by the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Manifest Your glory, and shame Your enemy.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>We lift up our hands and call on You.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>Amen.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>In this special conference, we want to see something higher than before.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>The inward reality is deeper, more far-reaching, and profound.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>The six verses in Ephesians 4:11-16 are the peak of the truth in the Lord s recovery.</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>Without the leading of the Lord and the revelation of the Bible, there is no way for us to understand them.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>What is an apostle?</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>What is a prophet?</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>What is an evangelist?</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>What is a shepherd and teacher?</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>How do these four kinds of gifts combine together to perfect the saints for the work of the ministry unto the building up of the Body of Christ?</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>How do we arrive at the oneness of the faith and of the full knowledge of the Son of God, at a full-grown man, and at the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ?</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>When you put these words together, seemingly you can understand all the words and phrases.</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>But when you put the six verses together, it is difficult to understand the meaning of them.</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>For this reason, tonight we have to ask the Lord to bring us to this peak of the Bible.</S>
   </TEXT>
